,Recommended,252670,7949057,"Posted: 6 December, 2013",all,Lana CtrlAltDel Rey,"Nihilumbra is about destruction. Basically the main character Is born in the void. He then leaves the void to live and see the world. However, the void follows him, creating monsters to slow/end his journey. He moves from location to location, damning each one by passing through it.Nihilumbra is a platformer/puzzle game. You spend most of the first campaign running and jumping with no combat ability. You never get a direct face to face combat option but you get a way to kill enemies. I think this adds to the appeal. Nihilumbra has some great platforming and some seriously challenging puzzles. Sometimes both are required.The gameplay involves color which you use to change the surfaces around you by clicking the mouse. During the main campaign the narrator will speak about what you're doing and question the nature of it.I loved the nihilistic tones and questions of meaning. Existing only to stay alive. Destroying things by your existance. It's a fun idea to explore.There's a second campaign that's hard as♥♥♥♥♥♥and  I haven't got very far in itBuy it."
