76561197971544967,Not Recommended,252670,33914696,Posted: 30 July,all,Blackblade,"This really isn't bad but there is nothing here that sets it above other games in my opinion.  It is a puzzle / platformer with a heavy emphasis on story, albeit a weird one.  It is also a very short game, at least for the first playthrough.Through the course of the game you learn abilities that you draw on surfaces that have various effects (the first makes things faster / easier to move for instance).  You use these to pass many obstacles along the way.  It is a nice concept and the first playthrough was fun enough for me, but I won't really remember it in a couple of weeks.  The controls work but once you start getting multiple abilities you have through cycle through in a short amout of time, they can be a burden (I was using mouse / keyboard).  The 2nd playthrough was very unfun due to this.  I decided to abandon the 2nd playthrough after a minute or so of playing it.  It started with a creature charging me which required immediate quick responses and the 2nd area continued the same.  If that is how it starts, I can only imagine what is coming later.  Just not worth the pain.  I suppose it is hard mode but there was no information on it, so no idea if there is a story or if it is only designed for diehards.So kind of nice for a while but there are just better things to spend your time / money on."
