,Recommended,252670,15331878,"Posted: 12 April, 2015",all,Mr Beard,"Honestely, this game is overlooked. And it's a crime.So what IS Nihilumbra? Without Spoiling anything, its about a little blob-thing (named Born, apparently) who tries to escape from the Void and make himself exist in the world. Does he suceed? Play the game. You'll find out.Gameplay-wise, it's a simple 2D Platformer/Puzzle game, implementing the use of different elements to continue your journey. Each element helps you in one particular way (e.g. brown makes you stick to walls/ceilings, red burns enemies and boxes, and so on). The main story is fairly simple, and can be completed in about an hour and a half or so. There is a harder mode called Void mode which does present a fairly difficult challenge, but wasn't as enjoying (at least, in my opinion).Visually, it's not bad. Not the best I've ever seen, but simple enough to do the job. It reminds me of Braid at times (the ""painting/storybook"" look).While I think the soundtrack isn't as memorable as other indie games, it is rather relaxing and easy on the ol' ear drums. I personally love the Void chase music.This is definitely a game that you want to take your time on, not because its difficult, but just to take it all in.The price is a bit over what I would pay for this kind of game (about $4-5), but if there's a sale, don't hesitate on picking it up. You won't regret it."
