,Recommended,252670,28760989,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,EspenTheStrange,"Overall, I would just barely recommend this game.At this point I have only finished the story mode, I have yet to try Void mode, but I wanted to center my review on the base game first.The first three colours you receive are fun, and slightly reminiscent of Element41, which is a game I really enjoyed. But the last two seemed like they had a vision for the game based on 5 colours and no ideas left. There could also be a much easier way to switch between colours, like using the number keys or cycling through using q and e.That coupled with what I thought was really weird voiceover work (both the voice acting and the writing) were the two main flaws of the game. The voiceover sounds like the guy from truck commercials trying to sound omniscient and he just came off sounding kinda bored. What made matters worse, voiceover-wise, was the writing. I would say the writing is by far the weakest facet of the game. It's too explanatory. What makes games like Element41 great to play was the simplicity in the explanation, and they didn't overuse the voice to further the plot. Nihilumbra felt the need to explain every metaphor to death and back.Now for the positives:The level design was interesting, especially towards the end where there could have been a few different ways to use the colours to move ahead in the level. The atmosphere is very neat, and the creatures from the void had some cool designs.All in all, I don't regret buying this game on sale for $2.39, I'm not sure I would pay the full $7.99 list price for it as a relatively poor person. Get it on sale if you can, see if you like it."
