,Recommended,252670,8526203,"Posted: 2 January, 2014",all,Bonkleton,"Some games are just fun, some tell a good story, and others can only be called works of art. Nihilumbra manages to be all three at once. The gameplay is satisfying as it blends tricky yet manageable platforming with puzzles involving physics-altering pigments. The story is charming at first, since you can not help but cheer for the little blob of life who has just been Born of nothingness, then slowly becomes more tragic as he is forced to bring death into the world around him simply by the act of surviving. Nihilumbra is also a beatiful artistic piece, sporting deep, ponderous themes and striking visuals both in the background and in the foreground. All these factors grip you and hold you so that you do not want to stop playing until it's done. I can't say for sure whether this game changed me as a person, but it certainly made a powerful impression on me. This is a wholehearted recommendation from one very impressed player."
