,Recommended,252670,13859574,"Posted: 5 January, 2015",all,D-Bag Johnson,"Nihilumbra is a 2D platformer with an extremely compelling art style and story.Story: Without spoiling too much in Nihilumbra you play as Born a being from the void and you set out to find your purpose while the void tries to stop you. In short this game has a great story and I encourage that you see for yourself.Gameplay: Nihilumbra is a 2D platformer were you must use colors to your advantage. Each color has a unique property that you can use to your advantage whether it's going through terrain, avoiding enemies or solving puzzles. In this game there is no way to kill enemies yourself until later in the game you also need to use your enviroment to help you. Using colors in my opinion was a great way to expand the depth in the gameplay and make it much less simple but not too complicated.Presentation: The art style of this game is beautiful. It really shows difference between the different levels you advance through and uses a wide range of colors. Not to mention that in this version there is now an art gallery where you can look at concept art, sketchs and level designs.Is it Good? There is one complaint I have about this game and thats how short it is if you play it fast it could be less then 3 hours of gameplay (not including Void mode). But besides that this hidden gem of an indie game is worth buying."
