76561198044334429,Recommended,252670,16047422,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,aquamantor,"Get it if it's on sale.Overall, not bad. But it seems like the creators saw these beautiful, story-rich art games catching on and wanted to make one so. very. desperately. The only thing the over-prevalent story can claim as its own is a narrator that won't shut up, telling you what you should feel on just about every screen, ultimately resulting in you feeling nothing. It doesn't help that the writing is poorly translated, and that the lone voice actor dutifully reads through typos as if they make as much sense to him as anything else in the script. (Honestly, given the fact that the guy had to say things like: ""Red possesses the power of fire"" that seems likely.) Someone missed the memo that games like this should omit text and voice acting entirely, unless it's borderline poetry.Now that that's out of the way, other artistic elements flourish. Honestly, I bought the game because of how gorgeous the screenshots looked, and it didn't disappoint visually all the way through. The animation, in particular, is extremely detailed, and it seems like every time you watch your character move, you see something you didn't notice before. All the backgrounds are equally pretty. The orchestral soundtrack is utterly fantastic, and the most surprising thing about the game (yes, it has an orchestral soundtrack). I just wish the developer had had the wisdom to let these elements speak for themselves.I know I'm mentioning the gameplay last, but personally, while it may have been easy, I thought the powers were a lot of fun to play with, and the mechanics for how they worked together were pretty well thought out. I haven't started Void mode yet, but I've heard it's when the game actually gets difficult, and that the 3 hour campaign is really just an extended tutorial. Honestly, I think it's a good format for a game with memorable mechanics, and this one has them. I'd love to see the game take advantage of the green and brown powers to make some insane platforming sequences. We'll have to see whether I'm disappointed or not later on."
