76561198102761464,Recommended,252670,15641197,"Posted: 1 May, 2015",all,JediKnightSky,"I havent played it for some time, and wanted to dwell on my thoughts of it before writing this. Because this game isnt just some quick play through in a few hours thoughtless run right platformer. I mean you do run endlessly right, and you do jump alot, but its so much more. It takes the legacy built upon for virtually the entire life of action sprite based side scrollers and takes it to something eye catchingly lovely while making you summon up the hand eye twitch skills that for many of us older gamers will take us back to the 80s and even before compared to many modern games that seem to cater to our ever aging and more casual needs.This game has story, that is a pleasure to hear the narration of as you flee from the very stuff you are born of. You now seek to LIVE fully and embrace the world in all its colors. You must keep one step ahead of that which you now must avoid at all cost, and gird yourself in the energies of life to move ever more effectively and even defeat those things which dare to bar your path. But in the end this is not a story of bringing meaningless death to masses of foes, no this is a game about bringing back life to a world that nearly dies for the price of your experiencing it."
