76561198278887605,Recommended,252670,22632630,"Posted: 25 April, 2016",all,ECGordon,"Hearing just nice things about this game, I've gone and tried it.I've to say, it was a bit less than I hoped for; even so, it was quite better than your average game.Playability is easy and nice in basic mode; a couple hours would be more than enough to finish the game from start to end. Graphics and general look are truly interesting, with almoust rough and unrefined backgrounds to nicely contrast with the cartoonish, well-contoured protagonist and its unsettling foes. There're more than a few moments when I honestly felt scared.Like I said, in basic mode the puzzles are quite simple - you need just a few tries to grasp the trick. There're lots of save points and not a whole heap of frustrating moments.And then, just when you thing you've done it and won the game, the Void mode falls upon you and, well, let's just say that I've spent right now twenty whole minutes stuck in the second level. The second level! There're, what, seventy levels? Eighty?I feel like I'll be playing Nihilumbra for a veeeeery long time.PROs:- Nice balance between easy mechanics and originality. It was your usual puzzle game, but with an interesting twist given by the possibility to mix colours.- Pretty aesthetics - and pretty animations. I loved the way your small Voidling shifted and sweated in the Volcano level; I loved the lava and I loved the soft, muted, dark colours of the Living Forest, the skeletons in the Ash Desert and the way the City felt truly electric. I felt both simple and home-made, someway, and truly cared for.- The fluidity. I was amazed by how truly un-monotonous it felt. Like, each level had its features and quirks, but it kept neverthless a fluid, uniform tone.- The Void Mode. I'm going to eviscerate it up to the very end, but I'll need to take my time. I went all, like, ahahah, nice game, boy, going to be done with you before dinner, and now I've to decide if I want to eat somewhen between now and, I don't know, next week? It's really NOT EASY. They've an Achievement saying so, too, the ""Void is hard"" Achievement.CONs:- The Yoda Wisdom. AKA, the game's attempt to stuff corny philosophy down your throat. Like, wow, no.- Too much writing and too much speaking. Sometimes they simply suggested to you how to pass the level - please, could you leave me some surprise? Same way, the spoken parts after a bit lost their feeling and became background noise. It's a pity.- The simplicity of the Story Mode. It was really and truly easy to win - but now I've the Void Mode to spend my nights with!An amateur will love the Story Mode; a skilled player will get mad with the levels of the Void Mode. I think almost everyone will be able to enjoy the aesthetic and the pleasant play. Fluid, dinamic, interesting: it's surely a very nice game and I feel like mine were well-spent money.I'd say, 7.5/10!"
