,Recommended,252670,21992810,"Posted: 22 March, 2016",all,Darkmayr,"Nihilumbra is a cute action platformer. It is definitely a puzzle game, and requires either a creative mind or an online guide for some of the harder levels.It is twice as long as it first appears, and you very much have to earn your happy ending. Nevertheless, it has a very well-told, if minimal, story. And it doesn't suffer for being minimal - the simplicity is actually part of what makes the story work.Its gameplay is simple to learn but it may take some time before you'll discover everything you can do with your powers. As a fairly uncreative person, I discovered some abilities entirely by accident and others only with the help of walkthroughs.The only reasonable complaint I can imagine is that it is clearly a port of a smartphone game - nevertheless, the port is VERY well done and I find that the controls work better on my computer than on my smartphone. It feels like the PC version was ported to smartphones, not vice-versa.After playing, I would be willing to pay twice the normal price for this game. If it's on sale, there is no reason to not buy it, and I think it's a steal even for the full $8.Overall 10/10"
