76561198062007743,Recommended,252670,22884047,"Posted: 9 May, 2016",all,Ghot,"Game's good, fun and long enough (completed it in 9 hrs including Void mode).The story and dialogs are nice and relatively deep. I personally really enjoyed them, especially with the narrator's great voice acting. It had me actually involved in the story and curious of knowing what's next. (Doesn't happen alot).The game is pretty easy by itself, for this reason the developers included ""Void mode"" (unlocked bybeating the first playtrough) which lets you replay the game with slight changes to the level layout and some of the enemies' behavior, drastically raising the overall difficulty of the game.Only real issue i've found is in the bullet physics, making them not bouncing where they are supposed to, (which can break the game sometimes) making the level completation impossible or way harder than it should be, but worry not:This can be fixed by playing the game in window mode disabling Vsync (this could make the game less enjoyable for the players with a high refresh rate monitorsFor such reasons I would advice playing the game in window mode, and Vsync on if you wish. When you feel like the bullets aren't bouncing where they are supposed to, turn Vsync off for the rest of the part/level.P.S: they took the time to convert every single text in the game (narrations and menu) in ""polygloth language"" which is a 10/10 by itself"
