76561198139234077,Recommended,252670,35433449,Posted: 2 October,all,Peregrin,"Nihilumbra is, as others have quite rightly pointed out, a masterpiece.  Although I only just bought the game on Steam, I've already played the iOS version, and it's one of the few games on iOS that I actually respect.  It was for this reason that I wanted to play it on PC, and from what I've played it's the same wonderful game I remember.  In fact, it's one of my favourite games of all time.  Very rarely does a game have a story that stirs the sort of emotions in me that Nihilumbra does.  While playing, Nihilumbra distinguishes itself from many other games by making one truly care about the protagonist Born, a being born from The Void.  A voice narrates Born's journey and his thoughts, making the player feel a connection to Born.  Over the course of the game, Born learns about the world and uses its power over colours to change it, all the while fleeing from The Void.  For my part I was invested every step of the way.In short, Nihilumbra is a unique and moving experience that you need to play at least once before you're taken by The Void."
,Not Recommended,252670,35479473,Posted: 4 October,all,kilian_smt,"When I first heard of Nihilumbra I was like ""Bless You"". Now that I have played trough it, I can confirm that this is true. The music gets really boring at some point, so you can't tell me, you would not be bored if you would have to listen to the same 2 minutes of music for 1 hour. So the mechanics are interesting And new. I like the system with the colors, but somehow, the delevopers got to mess this up as well. The puzzles soon start to get repetitive and in the last world, the will to beat this game was smaller as the price of it. Price? Hell yeah!Should you buy it for 6 bucks?No.Should you buy it for 2 bucks as I did?Maybe...Even if this game doesn't get you to want to beat it, it is really nice to relax and just like fall into it. The game is easy as hell. For 6 bucks nearly 3 hours of play time? Great! For 2 bucks the same? Even better!"
